Introduction¶

In this project,I have chosen the TDMB movies dataset.
In this section we will import the required packages.

Following questions can be analysed from the selected dataset:

  1. Which genres are most popular(top 10 genres)?
  2. Which movie has the highest and lowest budgets?
  3. Which movie has the most and least earned revenu?
  4. What is the average runtime of movie?
  5. What is the average budget of movie?
  6. What is the average revenue of the movie?
  7. Which movie has the most and least profit?
  8. Which movie has the highest and lowest vote_average ?
  9. What is the average vote_avearge of movie?
  10. Which cast has done the most of the movies?
  11. Which production has done the most of the movies?
  12. Which production has make the most profit?
  13. Which rating has make the most money?

In [24]:
#The below function is used to seprate the values of genres that have "|" as a seprator
def seprator(col):
    sep_values = df[col].str.cat(sep="|").split("|")
    count_sep_values =pd.Series(sep_values).value_counts(ascending=False)
    return count_sep_values    
count_genres= seprator("genres")

Research Question 2 (Which movie with largest and lowest budgets?)¶

In [26]:
# We will use this function many times to find the maximun and minimum values
def find_Max_Min(col):
    
    #finding the max and min vvalues in the column.
    Max_index=df[col].idxmax()
    Min_index=df[col].idxmin()
    #getting all the related columns of that max and min
    maximum=pd.DataFrame(df.loc[Max_index])
    minimum=pd.DataFrame(df.loc[Min_index])
    result=pd.concat([maximum,minimum],axis=1)
    return result

Conclusions¶

We came up with the following analysis:

  1. The genre of the movie should be one of these:
    1. Drama
    2. Comedy
    3. Thriller
    4. Action
    5. Advanture
  2. The top 5 casts are:
    1. Robert De Niro
    2. Bruce Willis
    3. Samuel L. Jackson
    4. Nicolas Cage
    5. Matt Damon
  3. The top 5 productions that have done most of the movies are:
    1. Universal Pictures
    2. Warner Bros.
    3. Paramount Pictures
    4. Twentieth Century Fox Film Corporation
    5. Columbia Pictures
  4. We analysed that the Column id with 2244 has the highest value in budget i.e. 425 million dollars (Movie : The Warrior's Way) whereas the column id with 2618 has the lowest value in budget i.e. 1 dollar (Movie : Lost & Found)
  5. We analysed that the Column id with 1386 is the highest in revenue i.e. 2.78 billion dollars (Movie : Avatar) while its budget is 237 million dollars whereas the column id with 5067 is the lowest in revenue i.e. 2 dollars while it's budget is 6 million dollars (Movie: Shattered Glass).
  6. The Shawshank Redemption has the highest votes i.e. 8.4 whereas Foodfight! has the lowest i.e. 2.2.
  7. We analysed that Avatar has earned the highest profit i.e. 2.54 billion dollars and The Warrior's Way has the lowest profit i.e. loss of 413.9 million dollars.
  8. To create a successful movie we analysed the following criteria:
    • Average duration of the movie must be 109.22 minutes.
    • Average Budget must be around 37.2 million dollars.
    • Average Revenue must be around 107.6 million dollar.
    • Average Vote must be around 6.17.
    • The cast must be from these:Robert De Niro, Bruce Willis, Samuel L. Jackson, Nicolas Cage and Matt Damon respectively.
    • The rating must be between 6.4 to 8.0
    • The producers must be from these: Walt Disney Pictures ,Pixar Animation Studios, Paramount Pictures, DreamsWorks Animation , Marvel Studio
  9. We analysed that The Walt Disney Pictures|Pixar Animation Studios production company have make the highest profit i.e. 5.79 billion profit.
  10. We analysed that the 6.5 rated movies have make 17.19 billion profit i.e. the highest amoung all other rating.
Limitations:
  1. We have dropped many rows with mssing values , hence a lot of information is also lost in that process
  2. Budget and Revenue do not have currency unit therefore we assumed it as dollars. It may also lead to futher errors because every country has its own currency which varies in foreign countries.
  3. We have also dropped many columns in the beginning that might helped later.
